title.narrative: New Element

description.narrative: UNICEF together with other nationwide partners ensured an uninterrupted availability of vaccines in the country. Vaccination was provided for 368,902 (82% of target) and 314,071 (70%) children under one year against DTP and measles respectively, and 488,613 (86%) children 6 months-15 years for measles in humanitarian situations. Furthermore 2,724,269 children (101%) received supplementary bOPV doses during April 2021 NIDs. DTP drop-out rates declined from 18% (2020) to 15% (2021). Health facilities with a functioning cold chain system increased from 757 to 881 (65%). In 2021, 178,368 people were fully vaccinated against COVID-19 and 85,378 took at least one dose. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:11/01/2022
